Class MyTweetWorker

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future<java.lang.String>, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture<java.lang.String>, twitter4j.StatusListener
public class MyTweetWorker
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
implements twitter4j.StatusListener

SwingWorker object, will handle starting the TwitterStream thread and post callbacks to the UI. (Hint: We should never update the widget/s state from anywhere but the event dispatch thread, the SwingWorker has a fancy method called "process" that queues on to the EDT, so any program updating Swing widgets from the SwingWorker process method should be considered fairly "thread safe")

Author:
andreas
